def_cn: 破旧不堪的;磨损的；用坏的
def_en: Something that is worn out is so old, damaged, or thin from use that it cannot be used any more.

def_cn: 疲惫不堪的;精疲力竭的
def_en: Someone who is worn out is extremely tired after hard work or a difficult or unpleasant experience.
If you describe something such as an idea as worn out, you mean that it is no longer relevant or interesting because it is old and has been repeated many times.
